Beginning in 2015, [[Saudi Arabian-led intervention in Yemen|Saudi Arabia led a coalition of forces]] to intervene in the [[Yemeni Civil War (2015–present)|civil war in Yemen]]. A number of aircraft, both helicopters and jets, have been lost due to accident or enemy action in the course of the campaign.
== 2015 == *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] 26 March 2015 - during the opening strikes, a Saudi [[McDonnell Douglas F-15E Strike Eagle|F-15S]] crashed into the Gulf of Aden after circling around over the sea; its two pilots ejected safely and were recovered from the sea by a USAF [[Sikorsky HH-60 Pave Hawk|HH-60G]] rescue helicopter. Arab coalition reports stated enemy fire did not cause the crash,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-rescues-saudi-pilots-from-crashed-fighter-jet-1427502224|title=U.S. Rescues Saudi Pilots from Crashed Fighter Jet|first=Julian E.|last=Barnes|date=28 March 2015|publisher=|via=www.wsj.com}}</ref> while Houthi and Iranian sources stated they shot it down.<ref>http://www.janes.com/article/50393/analysis-initial-saudi-air-strikes-lacked-intensity</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-rescues-two-saudi-fighter-pilots-after-splashdown-near-n331711|publisher=NBC News|title=U.S. Rescues Two Saudi Fighter Pilots After Splashdown Near Yemen|date=27 March 2015|access-date=27 March 2015}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of the Royal Moroccan Air Force.svg|20px|Roundel of the Royal Moroccan Air Force]] 10 May 2015 - at 18:00 local time, one Royal Moroccan Air Force [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16C Block 52]], serial number 08-8008, crashed in Saadah, while performing a mission as part of the Saudi-led intervention in Yemen. The pilot of a second F-16 said that he did not see any ejection. Originally missing for several hours,<ref name="news.yahoo.com">{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/moroccan-f-16-jet-saudi-led-coalition-yemen-095027491.html|title=Moroccan F-16 jet from Saudi-led coalition in Yemen crashes|date=11 May 2015|work=Yahoo News|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> on 11 May, the Shia rebels showed the crash site, located near Nushoor, Sa'ada. They claimed they shot the jet down with [[anti-aircraft artillery]] fire,<ref name="news.yahoo.com"/> while the pilot was killed in the crash.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f-16.net/f-16-news-article4947.html|title=Moroccan F-16 crashes over Yemen|work=f-16.net|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> According to [[Tom Cooper (author)|Tom Cooper]], the F-16 was shot down by Anti-Aircraft guns or [[MANPADS]].<ref name="warisboring.com">{{cite web|url=http://warisboring.com/the-houthis-do-it-yourself-air-defenses-2/|title=The Houthis’ Do-It-Yourself Air Defenses|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-yemen-security-clashes-idUKKBN0NW0IX20150511|title=Moroccan F-16 jet from Saudi-led coalition in Yemen crashes|first=Mohammed Ghobari and Mohammed|last=Mukhashaf|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] May 2015 - A Saudi AH-64 Helicopter was shot down by Houthis. *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] ('''2''') August 2015 - Two Saudi AH-64s crashed in Jizan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-mideast-yemen-crash-idUKKCN0QQ29P20150821|title=Two pilots killed when helicopter comes down on Saudi-Yemen border – coalition|first=Reuters|last=Editorial|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] September 2015 - One Saudi Apache helicopter was shot down.<ref name="auto3">{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20150921-houthis-claim-responsibility-for-fall-of-coalition-plane/|title=Houthis claim responsibility for fall of coalition plane|date=21 September 2015|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Bahrain.svg|20px|Roundel of Bahrain]] 30 December 2015 - a Bahraini [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16C]] crashed in [[Jizan Region]], Saudi Arabia. A military source reported that the pilot ejected and survived the crash. The F-16 was already in flames before hitting the ground as recorded on video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theaviationist.com/2016/01/04/bahrain-air-force-f-16-down/|title=Amateur video shows Bahraini F-16 already in flames before hitting the ground in Saudi Arabia|date=3 January 2016|publisher=}}</ref> The loss was initially attributed to a technical malfunction, but according to [[Tom Cooper (author)|Tom Cooper]], the F-16 was instead shot down by Anti-Aircraft guns or [[MANPADS]].<ref name="warisboring.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/bahrain-f-16-crashes-saudi-near-yemen-border-coalition-2000625843?|title=Bahrain F-16 crashes in Saudi near Yemen border after 'technical issue'|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref>
== 2016 == *[[File:Roundel of the United Arab Emirates.svg|20px|Roundel of the United Arab Emirates]] 14 March 2016 - a United Arab Emirates Dassault [[Mirage 2000|Mirage 2000-9D]] crashed in the southern Yemeni city of Aden during a combat operation in the early morning hours, killing its two pilots. The coalition claimed the Mirage crashed due to a technical fault.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.defensenews.com/global/mideast-africa/2016/03/14/uae-mirage-fighter-jet-crashes-over-yemen/|title=UAE Mirage Fighter Jet Crashes Over Yemen|first=Awad|last=Mustafa|date=8 August 2017|publisher=}}</ref> Other sources reported that the Mirage 2000-9D was shot down while flying low by [[Al-Qaeda insurgency in Yemen|Yemeni Al-Qaeda militants]] using a [[9K32 Strela-2|Strela-2]] [[MANPADS]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/yemen-conflict-al-qaeda-used-surface-to-air-missile-to-bring-down-emirati-fighter-jet-a6954671.html|title=Al-Qaeda ‘used surface-to-air missile’ to bring down Emirati fighter jet in Yemen|date=26 March 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-yemen-security-emirates/uae-armed-forces-say-missing-fighter-jet-in-yemen-state-media-idUSKCN0WG0DJ|title=UAE plane crashed in Yemen due to technical fault, pilots killed: coalition|date=14 March 2016|accessdate=30 October 2017|agency=Reuters}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of the United Arab Emirates.svg|20px|Roundel of the United Arab Emirates]] ('''2''') June 2016 - Two UAE helicopters, one AH-64 and one [[Bell 407|NSA 407MRH]], crashed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence-blog.com/news/uae-helicopter-crash-in-yemen-kills-2-crew-members.html|title=UAE helicopter crash in Yemen kills 2 crew members – Defence Blog|first=Dylan|last=Malyasov|website=defence-blog.com|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] July 2016 - One Saudi AH-64 crashed in Marib<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.janes.com/article/62552/saudi-arabia-says-apache-crashed-in-yemen|title=Saudi Arabia says Apache crashed in Yemen|access-date=30 October 2017}}</ref>
== 2017 == *[[File:Roundel of Jordan.svg|20px|Roundel of Jordan]] 24 February 2017 - a Jordanian [[General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon|F-16]] crashed in [[Najran]], Saudi Arabia, a military source reported that the pilot survived the crash.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/website-jordanian-16-jet-crashed-saudi-arabia-45711653|title=ABC News|first=ABC|last=News|website=ABC News}}</ref> Houthis claimed to have shot down the aircraft.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.presstv.ir/Detail/2017/02/24/511901/Yemeni-forces-allies-shooting-down-Jordanian-jet-Saudi-Arabia-Najran|title=PressTV-‘Yemeni forces shoot down Jordanian F-16’|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gulf-times.com/story/534158/Jordan-warplane-crashes-in-Saudi-pilot-survives|title=Jordan warplane crashes in Saudi, pilot survives|date=24 February 2017|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of the USAF.svg|25px|Roundel of the USAF]] February 2017 - A US [[UAV]] MQ-9 shot down<ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence-blog.com/news/houthi-militants-claim-to-shut-down-mq-9-reaper-uav-over-marib-in-yemen.html|title=Houthi Militants Claim to Shut Down MQ-9 Reaper UAV Over Marib in Yemen – Defence Blog|first=Dylan|last=Malyasov|website=Defence-Blog.com|access-date=7 November 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] March 2017 - Saudi AH-64 (2 dead)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2017/3/16/yemens-houthi-rebels-shoot-down-apache-helicopter-in-hodeida|title=Yemen's Houthi rebels 'shoot down Apache helicopter in Hodeida'|first=The New|last=Arab|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> *[[File:Roundel of Saudi Arabia.svg|20px|Roundel of Saudi Arabia]] April 2017 - Saudi UH-60 downed in Marib (12 dead)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/yemen/12-saudi-soldiers-martyred-in-yemen-helicopter-crash-1.2013716|title=12 Saudi soldiers martyred in Yemen helicopter crash|last=Agencies|date=18 April 2017|access